1956;;Jumping for Joy;;British;;John Paddy Carstairs;;Frankie Howerd, Stanley Holloway;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jumping_for_Joy;;A man buys a greyhound and enters it in a major race, but discovers the dog has one paw in the grave. As our hero nurses the pooch back to health, he also gets mixed up with criminals who want to fix the race by doping dogs.[1][2]